===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|dʰeh₁}}
From {{inh|en|enm|demen|dẹ̄men|to judge; to criticize, condemn; to impose a penalty on, sentence; to direct, order; to believe, think, deem}}, from {{inh|en|ang|dēman||to decide, decree, deem, determine, judge; to condemn, doom, sentence; to consider, examine, reckon, think; to prove; to compute, estimate; to declare, tell; to glorify, praise}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=dẹ̄men, v.|id=MED11023|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref> from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*dōmijaną||to judge, think}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dʰeh₁-||to set, put}}. The word is cognate with {{cog|da|dømme||to judge}}, {{cog|nl|doemen||to condemn, foredoom}}, {{cog|frr|dema||to judge, recognise}}, {{cog|nb|dømme||to judge}}, {{cog|nn|døma||to judge}}, {{cog|sv|döma||to judge, sentence, condemn}}. It is also related to {{m|en|doom}}.<ref>{{R:Oxford Dictionaries Online}}</ref>

